<abstract>
<t>The Point-to-Point Protocol (PPP)provides a standard method for transporting multi-protocol datagrams over point-to-point links.
   The PPP Compression Control Protocolprovides a method to negotiate and utilize compression protocols over PPP encapsulated links. This document describes the use of the Stac LZS data compression algorithm for compressing PPP encapsulated packets, using a DCP header. This protocol is an enhanced version of the non-DCP (Option 17) PPP Stac LZS compression protocol, and will be referred to as the LZS-DCP Compression Protocol.</t></abstract></front>

